fix: RFC-001 spec + systematic RFC audit tooling

RFC-001 failed at Step 4 in first real execution attempt: `uv sync --frozen`
rejected `[tool.uv] default-groups = ["dev"]` because the project's dev deps
live in PEP 621 `[project.optional-dependencies]`, not PEP 735
`[dependency-groups]`. This commit fixes that specific spec AND audits every
other full-fleshed RFC for similar class-of defects.

RFC-001 fix:
- Step 2: remove `[tool.uv] default-groups = ["dev"]` line (kept
  `[[tool.uv.index]]` mirrors).
- Step 4: `uv sync --frozen` -> `uv sync --frozen --all-extras` so dev deps
  still install via the optional-dependencies mechanism.
- Notes for executor: document the PEP 621 / PEP 735 incompatibility.

Systematic audit (10 of 15 full-fleshed RFCs fail pre-flight):

New tooling:
- `scripts/validate_rfc.py` (350 LOC): 10 checks C1-C10 covering front-matter
  integrity, files_to_read existence, SEARCH-block uniqueness, WRITE collision
  detection, RUN whitelist enforcement, budget caps, blocking_on validity.
  Runs in <1s against all RFCs. Parses raw YAML to recover `# new` /
  `# modified` comments that `safe_load` drops.

New documents:
- `RFC_AUDIT_PREFLIGHT.md` (500 LOC): per-RFC verdict with 5-class defect
  taxonomy (config hallucination, phantom file reference, SEARCH block
  hallucination, missing from files_will_touch, budget cap overrun). 24 real
  errors catalogued, each with location + minimum fix.
- `SPEC_AUTHORING_CHECKLIST.md` (250 LOC): 12-section checklist authors must
  tick before submitting an RFC. Guards against the 5 defect classes.

Protocol tightening:
- AGENT_EXECUTION_PROTOCOL §5.0 NEW: mandatory `validate_rfc.py` run before
  Step 1 of any RFC execution. Exit non-zero = abort.
- exec/rfc/ skill Step 3: validator is now part of the pre-flight trio
  (git status + full_verify + validate_rfc).
- audit/rfc/ skill Step 0: machine pre-flight as the first review action.

INDEX.md status updates per audit:
- RFC-003, RFC-006, RFC-010, RFC-A04, RFC-T00, RFC-T08: `blocked` with
  reason `spec_failed_preflight` (SEARCH hallucination / phantom paths /
  budget overrun). Require rewrite.
- RFC-007, RFC-008, RFC-009: `blocked-dep` (transitively depend on RFC-006).

Regression:
- full_verify.py still 8/8 green (no src/ code changes).
- Validator: 5 pass, 10 fail (23 errors, 8 warnings).
- RFC-001 now PASS after fix.

Next: human rewrites RFC-A04/T00/T08 SEARCH blocks against real files,
then attempts exec/rfc/ again. Any new RFC must pass validate_rfc.py
before landing.
